    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka President appoints committee to probe Taisei-linked allegation",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka President Ranil Wickremesinghe has appointed a committee headed by a retired High Court judge to probe an allegation that a minister had demanded a bribe from Japan\u2019s Taisei construction company.",
        "Former Minister Nimal Siripala de Silva had requested a formal investigation after opposition leader Sajith Premadada made the allegation in parliament and there were also social media reports, the President\u2019s media office said.",
        "Though a minister was not named, de Silva said Taisei was involved in a Colombo airport contract, and by implication the allegations pointed to him and wanted a formal probe.",
        "The committee will be headed by Retired High Court Judge and President\u2019s Counsel Kusala Sarojini Weerawardena.",
        "Retired Senior Deputy Inspector General of Police S M Wickremasinghe, a retired Special Grade Officer of Sri Lanka Administrative Service S M G K Perera will be the other two members.",
        "Minister de Silva resigned after the allegation was made, denying any involvement."
      ],
